description.plain:
Helping define the sound of EDM in the mid-2010s with his combination of hip-hop and electronic dance music, DJ Snake (born William Sami Étienne Grigahcine) is a French DJ and producer of Algerian origin.

Born to a French father and an Algerian mother, he grew up in a Parisian ghetto, where he earned the ‘Snake’ moniker for his ability to escape police for his graffiti. By the age of fourteen he began DJing before picking up producing when he was nineteen, combining his backgrounds in hip-hop and electronic dance music.

He first gained attention for his work on Lady Gaga’s album Born This Way, which earned him a Grammy nomination for Album of the Year. His mainstream breakthrough followed a few years later with his 2013 single “Turn Down for What”, an EDM-trap song that peaked at #4 on the Billboard Hot 100, ultimately becoming the twelfth biggest EDM song of the 2010s.

The massive success of this song was replicated in the following years by a slew of hits including the top five hits “Lean On” with Major Lazer and MØ and “Let Me Love You” with Justin Bieber, as well as the top twenty hits “Taki Taki” with Selena Gomez, Ozuna, and Cardi B, “You Know You Like It” with AlunaGeorge, and “Middle” with Bipolar Sunshine.

To date, he has certified album sales of 1.5 million and certified singles sales of 33.5 million in the United States alone.

description.plain: “Let Me Love You” is Biebs' ode to a girl who seems ready to put an end to their relationship.  Over smooth tropical production from DJ Snake, Bieber pleads with his lover to stick around and receive his love. This subject matter has become a popular topic in Justin’s music as seen on 2015’s Purpose and his feature on Major Lazer’s  2016 hit “Cold Water.”

description.plain:
“Taki Taki” is a DJ Snake produced song influenced by Reggaeton, featuring a trio with Latin roots: Ozuna, Cardi B and Selena Gomez, singing in both Spanish and English.

In the song, the artists talk about dancing and the possibility of how love could go much farther through dancing and teasing. Taki Taki has no official meaning, and it is believed that is used in the song just for better sound.

The rumors of this joint song first surfaced on 25 August 2018 when DJ Snake posted a photo on social media showing director stools for the four artists (plus Cardi’s daughter), teasing the collaboration between them.

https://twitter.com/djsnake/status/1033155101517479936

The song was confirmed to be about 6 minutes prior to its release. But in fact the song only lasts for 3:32 after the release. Whether the song has ever been 6 minutes long before may never be truly resolved.

description.plain:
The first single off DJ Snake’s debut album Encore features vocalist Bipolar Sunshine who ruminates on how he has hurt his lover, and offers to make up for his mistakes.

Bipolar told CUB:

I’m a hopeless romantic. I talk about every day life. Breakups. Everyone goes through breakups.
